---
description: Capture every fixed bug as a permanent regression test
alwaysApply: false
---

# Write regression tests

- Every fixed bug gets a test that **would have failed before the fix**.
- Reference the issue / PR in the test name or a one-line comment.
- Reproduce the original input; assert the corrected output or behavior.
- Place the test next to the unit it protects; tag as `regression` if your runner supports it.
- Keep tight scope—one regression per test; resist generalizing it.
- Don't delete regression tests during refactors unless the bug class is impossible by construction.
